{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1142,"text":"It's Christmas Eve, 1968."},{"time":5520,"text":"The Apollo 8 spacecraft\nhas successfully completed"},{"time":8960,"text":"its first three orbits around the moon."},{"time":12960,"text":"Launched from Cape Canaveral\nthree days before,"},{"time":15680,"text":"this is the first time"},{"time":17400,"text":"that humans have ever traveled\nbeyond low Earth orbit."},{"time":22440,"text":"On the vessel's fourth pass,"},{"time":24480,"text":"the Earth slowly comes into view"},{"time":27200,"text":"and reveals itself\nabove the Moon's horizon."},{"time":31680,"text":"Astronaut Bill Anders frantically\nasks his crewmates where their camera is,"},{"time":35640,"text":"grabs the Hasselblad,\npoints it towards the window,"},{"time":38080,"text":"presses the shutter,"},{"time":39440,"text":"and takes one of the most\nimportant photographs of all time:"},{"time":44560,"text":"\"Earthrise.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":46720,"text":"When the crew was safely home\na few days later,"},{"time":49400,"text":"they were asked about the mission."},{"time":51960,"text":"Anders famously replied,"},{"time":54240,"text":"\"We went to the moon,"},{"time":56360,"text":"but we actually discovered Earth.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":61480,"text":"What did he and his fellow crewmates feel"},{"time":65800,"text":"in this incredible moment?"},{"time":67840,"text":"In a study released just this past year,"},{"time":70400,"text":"a team of researchers\nat the University of Pennsylvania"},{"time":73480,"text":"examined the testimonies\nof hundreds of astronauts"},{"time":77120,"text":"who had the opportunity\nto view the Earth from space."},{"time":80400,"text":"Their analysis uncovered\nthree common feelings:"},{"time":84200,"text":"first, a greater appreciation\nfor Earth's beauty;"},{"time":88000,"text":"second, an increased sense\nof connection to all other living beings;"},{"time":93120,"text":"and third, an unexpected,\noften overwhelming sense of emotion."},{"time":99160,"text":"The researchers believe that seeing\nthe Earth from a great distance"},{"time":102640,"text":"provokes someone to develop\nnew cognitive frameworks"},{"time":106600,"text":"to understand what they are seeing."},{"time":109240,"text":"They believe these astronauts\nwere forever changed"},{"time":112240,"text":"by this new view,"},{"time":114120,"text":"this new perspective,"},{"time":116040,"text":"this new visual truth."},{"time":119360,"text":"This feeling is commonly referred to\nas the \"overview effect.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":125120,"text":"Only 558 people\nhave ever been to outer space."},{"time":130199,"text":"558 people had the opportunity"},{"time":133360,"text":"to gaze down in awe,"},{"time":136520,"text":"to wonder at our planet"},{"time":138200,"text":"floating in an infinite sea of darkness."},{"time":141840,"text":"But what if that number were bigger?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144640,"text":"Three years ago,\nI set off on my own mission:"},{"time":148160,"text":"to see if I could bring this feeling\nof overwhelming scale and beauty"},{"time":152920,"text":"to many more people"},{"time":154600,"text":"just by using one small computer"},{"time":156680,"text":"in my small New York City apartment."},{"time":159480,"text":"It was then, in 2013,\nthat I launched \"Daily Overview.\""},{"time":163520,"text":"Every day, I have used satellite imagery"},{"time":167080,"text":"to create one expansive\noverhead view of our planet."},{"time":171480,"text":"More than 1,000 of these images\nhave been created thus far,"},{"time":176440,"text":"and more than 600,000 people"},{"time":178960,"text":"tune in for this daily dose\nof perspectives."},{"time":182040,"text":"I create the imagery by curating photos\nfrom the massive archive"},{"time":187160,"text":"of a satellite company\ncalled Digital Globe."},{"time":190080,"text":"They operate a constellation\nof five satellites,"},{"time":192880,"text":"each roughly the size of an ambulance,"},{"time":195520,"text":"that is constantly\ntaking pictures of the Earth"},{"time":197960,"text":"as they orbit at\n28,000 kilometers per hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203280,"text":"Now, what does this mean?"},{"time":205600,"text":"Each of these satellites\nis equipped with a camera"},{"time":208000,"text":"that has a focal length of 16 meters,"},{"time":210920,"text":"so that's roughly 290 times greater"},{"time":214640,"text":"than a DSLR camera equipped\nwith a standard 55 millimeter lens."},{"time":219800,"text":"So if were able to attach\none of their satellites"},{"time":222280,"text":"to the roof of this theater in Oxford,"},{"time":225200,"text":"we could take a picture of a football,"},{"time":228000,"text":"clearly, on the pitch\nat the stadium in Amsterdam."},{"time":233040,"text":"That's 450 kilometers away."},{"time":236560,"text":"That's incredibly powerful technology."},{"time":239520,"text":"And I decided at the beginning\nof this project"},{"time":242040,"text":"that I would use\nthat incredible technology"},{"time":244520,"text":"to focus on the places"},{"time":246440,"text":"where humans have impacted the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250120,"text":"As a species, we dig and scrape\nthe Earth for resources,"},{"time":254520,"text":"we produce energy,"},{"time":256680,"text":"we raise animals\nand cultivate crops for food,"},{"time":260880,"text":"we build cities, we move around,"},{"time":263360,"text":"we create waste."},{"time":264720,"text":"And in the process\nof doing all of these things,"},{"time":268040,"text":"we shape landscapes and seascapes"},{"time":271160,"text":"and cityscapes with increasing\ncontrol and impunity."},{"time":276640,"text":"So with that in mind,"},{"time":277920,"text":"I would like to share\na few of my overviews with you now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281680,"text":"Here we see cargo ships and oil tankers"},{"time":285200,"text":"waiting outside the entry\nto the port of Singapore."},{"time":288880,"text":"This facility is the second-busiest\nin the world by terms of total tonnage,"},{"time":293840,"text":"accounting for one-fifth\nof the world's shipping containers"},{"time":297240,"text":"and one half of the annual supply"},{"time":299720,"text":"of crude oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301800,"text":"If you look closely at this overview,\nyou'll see a lot of little specks."},{"time":305720,"text":"Those are actually cows at a feedlot"},{"time":308600,"text":"in Summerfield, Texas,\nin the United States."},{"time":312080,"text":"So once cows reach a particular weight,"},{"time":314320,"text":"roughly 300 kilograms,"},{"time":316480,"text":"they are moved here\nand placed on a specialized diet."},{"time":319960,"text":"Over the next three to four months,\nthe cows gain an additional 180 kilograms"},{"time":325120,"text":"before they are shipped off to slaughter."},{"time":327280,"text":"You're also probably wondering\nabout this glowing pool at the top there."},{"time":330720,"text":"That gets its color from a unique\ncombination of manure, chemicals"},{"time":334600,"text":"and a particular type of algae\nthat grows in the stagnant water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339160,"text":"This is the Mount Whaleback iron ore mine"},{"time":342000,"text":"in the Pilbara region\nof Western Australia,"},{"time":345320,"text":"a beautiful yet scary scar\non the face of the Earth."},{"time":349160,"text":"Of the world's mined iron ore,"},{"time":351240,"text":"98 percent is used to make steel"},{"time":354200,"text":"and is therefore a major component\nin the construction of buildings,"},{"time":357520,"text":"automobiles or appliances\nsuch as your dishwasher or refrigerator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363240,"text":"This is a solar concentrator\nin Seville, Spain."},{"time":366880,"text":"So this facility contains 2,650 mirrors"},{"time":371600,"text":"which are arrayed in concentric circles\naround an 140-meter-tall tower"},{"time":376680,"text":"at its center."},{"time":378480,"text":"At the top of the tower,"},{"time":379960,"text":"there is a capsule of molten salt"},{"time":382200,"text":"that gets heated by the beams\nof light reflected upwards"},{"time":385840,"text":"from the mirrors below."},{"time":387800,"text":"From there, the salt circulates\nto a storage tank underground,"},{"time":391280,"text":"where it produces steam,"},{"time":392760,"text":"which spins turbines"},{"time":394240,"text":"and generates enough electricity\nto power 70,000 homes"},{"time":397760,"text":"and offsets 30,000 tons\nof carbon dioxide emissions every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403200,"text":"This overview shows deforestation\nin Santa Cruz, Bolivia"},{"time":407240,"text":"immediately adjacent\nto untouched tracts of rainforest."},{"time":412212,"text":"Deforestation in the country\nhas primarily been driven"},{"time":414760,"text":"by the expansion of mechanized agriculture"},{"time":417400,"text":"and cattle ranching,"},{"time":419080,"text":"so as the country tries to meet\nthe demand of its growing population"},{"time":422320,"text":"and feed them,"},{"time":423560,"text":"the sacrificial destruction\nof its rainforest"},{"time":425880,"text":"has taken place to do so."},{"time":428160,"text":"It is estimated that the country\nlost 4.5 million acres of rainforest"},{"time":433160,"text":"in one decade alone"},{"time":434640,"text":"from 2000 until 2010."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437920,"text":"This is the Eixample district\nin Barcelona, Spain."},{"time":441640,"text":"So the overview perspective\ncan be incredibly helpful"},{"time":444440,"text":"to help us understand how cities function"},{"time":446480,"text":"and how we can devise\nsmarter solutions for urban planning,"},{"time":449440,"text":"and this will become only more relevant"},{"time":451600,"text":"as it is expected that 4.9 billion people\nwill live in cities around the world"},{"time":457120,"text":"by the year 2030."},{"time":459240,"text":"This area of Barcelona is characterized\nby its strict grid pattern,"},{"time":463480,"text":"apartments with communal courtyards"},{"time":465520,"text":"and these octagonal intersections"},{"time":467720,"text":"which allow for more sunlight,\nbetter ventilation"},{"time":470760,"text":"and additional parking at street level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473480,"text":"And here we see that grid pattern\nbut under much different circumstances."},{"time":478480,"text":"This is the Dadaab Refugee Camp\nin northern Kenya,"},{"time":482000,"text":"the largest such facility\nof its kind in the world."},{"time":484960,"text":"To cope with the influx of refugees\nwho are fleeing Somalia,"},{"time":488240,"text":"where there is famine and conflict,"},{"time":490160,"text":"the UN has built this area\ngridded out at left"},{"time":492680,"text":"called the LFO extension"},{"time":494440,"text":"to house more and more refugees"},{"time":496000,"text":"who are arriving and occupying\nthese white dots,"},{"time":499000,"text":"which are actually tents"},{"time":500360,"text":"which will slowly fill up\nthe area over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503480,"text":"So if you have one of these overviews,"},{"time":506600,"text":"you have a moment in time."},{"time":509280,"text":"If we have two overviews, however,"},{"time":511160,"text":"we are able to tell stories\nabout changes in time."},{"time":514760,"text":"I call that feature\nof the project \"Juxtapose,\""},{"time":517120,"text":"and we'll share a few examples\nof it with you now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520240,"text":"So the tulip fields in Netherlands\nbloom every year in April."},{"time":525120,"text":"So we take an image\ncaptured in March a few weeks before"},{"time":528280,"text":"and contrast it to one\ntaken a few weeks later."},{"time":531560,"text":"We're able to watch the flowers bloom\nin this magnificent cascade of color."},{"time":537040,"text":"It is estimated that the Dutch produce\n4.3 billion tulip bulbs every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544160,"text":"In 2015, two dams collapsed"},{"time":547280,"text":"at an iron ore mine\nin southeastern Brazil,"},{"time":550000,"text":"causing one of the worst\nenvironmental disasters"},{"time":552640,"text":"in the history of the country."},{"time":554480,"text":"It is estimated that 62 million\ncubic meters of waste"},{"time":558400,"text":"were released when the dams broke,"},{"time":560120,"text":"destroying numerous villages\nin the process,"},{"time":562560,"text":"including Bento Rodrigues,\nseen here before ..."},{"time":568120,"text":"and after the flood."},{"time":571280,"text":"Ultimately, 19 people\nwere killed in this disaster."},{"time":574840,"text":"Half a million people did not\nhave access to clean drinking water"},{"time":577960,"text":"for an extended period of time,"},{"time":580000,"text":"and the waste soon entered\ninto the Doce River,"},{"time":582480,"text":"extended for 650 kilometers"},{"time":585000,"text":"all the way into the sea,"},{"time":586680,"text":"killing unknowable amounts\nof plant and animal life along the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591440,"text":"And lastly, here is a story\nrelated to the crisis in Syria,"},{"time":595240,"text":"a conflict which has claimed the lives\nof hundreds of thousands of people"},{"time":599120,"text":"and displaced millions."},{"time":601040,"text":"So this patch of desert\nis seen in Mafraq, Jordan in 2011,"},{"time":605560,"text":"the year the conflict started,"},{"time":607280,"text":"and when we compare it to an image\ncaptured just this year in 2017,"},{"time":612720,"text":"we see the construction\nof the Zaatari refugee camp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616040,"text":"So just as the astronauts of Apollo 8"},{"time":619720,"text":"watched the Earth rising above\nthe lunar landscape for the first time,"},{"time":623680,"text":"there is no way\nthat you could have imagined"},{"time":625880,"text":"what the places I just showed you\nlook like from outer space."},{"time":630720,"text":"And while you may enjoy\nthe aesthetics of an image,"},{"time":633440,"text":"once you learn exactly\nwhat it is you're seeing,"},{"time":635720,"text":"you may struggle with the fact\nthat you still like it."},{"time":639480,"text":"And that's the tension\nI want to create with my work,"},{"time":642320,"text":"because I believe\nit is that contemplation,"},{"time":645480,"text":"that internal dialogue"},{"time":647440,"text":"that will lead to greater\ninterest in our planet"},{"time":649880,"text":"and more awareness\nof what we're doing to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652960,"text":"I believe that viewing the Earth\nfrom the overview perspective"},{"time":655920,"text":"is more important now than ever before."},{"time":659440,"text":"Through the incredible technology\nof these high-flying cameras,"},{"time":662800,"text":"we can see, monitor and expose"},{"time":666000,"text":"the unprecedented impact\nthat we are having."},{"time":669360,"text":"And whether we are scientists"},{"time":671400,"text":"or engineers or policymakers"},{"time":674440,"text":"or investors or artists,"},{"time":677400,"text":"if we can adopt\na more expansive perspective,"},{"time":680880,"text":"embrace the truth of what is going on"},{"time":684200,"text":"and contemplate the long-term\nhealth of our planet,"},{"time":688360,"text":"we will create a better"},{"time":690360,"text":"and safer and smarter future"},{"time":693160,"text":"for our one and only home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695320,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696560,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}